# rh.lean вАФ Phases CXXXвАУCXXXI: the overflow-residue engine and its polynomial instantiation

The decisive operator of overflow calculus is the logarithmic derivative
  ќЫ[f](z) := f'(z) / f(z).
For a factored object it expands as a signed residue cloud
  ќЫ[f](z) = ќ£_j m_j / (z вИТ r_j) вИТ ќ£_k n_k / (z вИТ p_k).
Real-rooted clouds satisfy the **anti-Herglotz** upper-half-plane sign law
  Im R(z) вЙ§ 0  for  Im z > 0,
since `Im 1/(z вИТ r) = вИТ(Im z)/|z вИТ r|¬≤ вЙ§ 0` for `r вИИ вДЭ`. A nonreal
upper-half-plane zero of `f` would force `ќЫ[f]` to escape upward there
(probe `ѕБ вИТ ќµ¬ЈI`), contradicting the law.

This file lands the **engine** (CXXX abstract layer) and its **polynomial
instantiation** (CXXXI). The active proof shape is:

  AntiHerglotz ќЫ[ќЮ]  +  pole-witness on ќЫ[ќЮ]
                     вЗТ  no upper-half-plane zeros of ќЮ
  +  ќЮ(zћД) = conj ќЮ(z)
                     вЗТ  every zero of ќЮ is real.

For polynomials this is fully proved end-to-end in ¬І7. For an abstract
target `ќЮ` it is fully proved in ¬І8 modulo three honest hypotheses.

