-- =====================================================================
-- ¬І12. Equivalent analytic targets for the xi anti-Herglotz sign law
--      (CXXXV)
-- =====================================================================
-- The single open analytic mountain is the sign law for `ќЫ[ќЮ]` on the
-- upper half-plane. This section defines the concrete `XiPullback`,
-- the named target `XiPullbackAntiHerglotzTarget`, and three equivalent
-- (or near-equivalent) reformulations:
--
--   вАҐ `XiHerglotzTarget` вАФ the Pick/Herglotz dual via negation.
--   вАҐ `XiLeftHalfLogDerivSignTarget` вАФ the s-plane reformulation, where
--     `s = ¬љ + i¬Јz` puts the xi formula in its natural shape.
--   вАҐ `XiPullbackEnergyMonotoneAwayFromZeros` вАФ the energy/modulus
--     monotonicity form, suitable for direct calculus or PDE attacks.
--
-- Plus a named placeholder for the integrated-kernel form
-- `XiKernelEnergyInequality` (the numerical evidence rules out pointwise
-- positivity of the kernel; an integrated/total-positivity statement is
-- the actual target).
--
-- This section adds ONLY targets and the easy general dualization. The
-- chain-rule iff between the z-plane and s-plane forms, the calculus
-- bridge from energy monotonicity to anti-Herglotz, and the kernel-form
-- bridge are all genuine analytic content вАФ they belong in later phases.

/-- The completed xi function
  ќЊ(s) = ¬љ ¬Ј s ¬Ј (s вИТ 1) ¬Ј ѕА^(вИТs/2) ¬Ј ќУ(s/2) ¬Ј ќґ(s).
Entire, with zeros exactly at the nontrivial Riemann-zeta zeros. -/
noncomputable def completedXiFunction (s : вДВ) : вДВ :=
  (1 / 2 : вДВ) * s * (s - 1)
    * Complex.exp (-(s / 2) * (Real.log Real.pi : вДВ))
    * Complex.Gamma (s / 2)
    * riemannZeta s

/-- The **critical-line pullback** `ќЮ(z) := ќЊ(¬љ + i¬Јz)`. The map
`z вЖ¶ ¬љ + i¬Јz` sends `z вИИ вДЭ` to the critical line `Re = ¬љ`, converting
RH into "all zeros of `XiPullback` are real". -/
noncomputable def XiPullback (z : вДВ) : вДВ :=
  completedXiFunction ((1 / 2 : вДВ) + Complex.I * z)

/-- **The xi anti-Herglotz target.** `Im(ќЫ[ќЮ] z) вЙ§ 0` for every `z` in
the open upper half-plane. The single genuinely open analytic content of
the programme. -/
def XiPullbackAntiHerglotzTarget : Prop :=
  AntiHerglotzUHP (logDerivativeResponse XiPullback)

/-- **Herglotz upper-half-plane sign law.** `Im(R z) вЙ• 0` on `Im z > 0`.
The classical Pick/Nevanlinna sign вАФ `R` maps the upper half-plane into
the closed upper half-plane. -/
def HerglotzUHP (R : вДВ вЖТ вДВ) : Prop :=
  вИА z : вДВ, 0 < z.im вЖТ 0 вЙ§ (R z).im

/-- **General dualization.** `R` is anti-Herglotz iff `вИТR` is Herglotz.
The whole programme can be stated either way; pick the form most natural
for the attack. -/
theorem negHerglotzUHP_iff_antiHerglotzUHP (R : вДВ вЖТ вДВ) :
    HerglotzUHP (fun z => -(R z)) вЖФ AntiHerglotzUHP R := by
  unfold HerglotzUHP AntiHerglotzUHP
  constructor
  ¬Ј intro h z hz
    have h' := h z hz
    simp at h'
    linarith
  ¬Ј intro h z hz
    have h' := h z hz
    simp
    linarith

/-- **Xi Herglotz target.** The Pick/Nevanlinna dual: `вИТќЫ[ќЮ]` is
Herglotz on the upper half-plane. -/
def XiHerglotzTarget : Prop :=
  HerglotzUHP (fun z => -(logDerivativeResponse XiPullback z))

/-- The two xi targets are equivalent via negation. -/
theorem XiHerglotzTarget_iff_XiPullbackAntiHerglotzTarget :
    XiHerglotzTarget вЖФ XiPullbackAntiHerglotzTarget :=
  negHerglotzUHP_iff_antiHerglotzUHP _

/-- **s-plane reformulation.** Under the change of variables
`s = ¬љ + i¬Јz`, the upper half-plane `Im z > 0` corresponds to the open
left half-strip `Re s < ¬љ`. The chain rule
`ќЫ[ќЮ](z) = i ¬Ј ќЫ[ќЊ](¬љ + i¬Јz)`
gives `Im(ќЫ[ќЮ](z)) = Re(ќЫ[ќЊ](s))`, so the anti-Herglotz target becomes
`Re(ќЫ[ќЊ](s)) вЙ§ 0` on `Re s < ¬љ`. This is the natural form for any
attack via the explicit ќЊ formula or the digamma decomposition. The
chain-rule iff with `XiPullbackAntiHerglotzTarget` is a calculus chase
deferred to a later phase. -/
def XiLeftHalfLogDerivSignTarget : Prop :=
  вИА s : вДВ, s.re < (1 / 2 : вДЭ) вЖТ
    ((deriv completedXiFunction s) / completedXiFunction s).re вЙ§ 0

/-- **Energy / modulus monotonicity target (away from zeros).**
`вИВ_y вАЦќЮ(x + i¬Јy)вАЦ¬≤  вЙ•  0` for `y > 0`, at points where `ќЮ` is nonzero.

Equivalent to the anti-Herglotz target (away from zeros) via the identity
`вИВ_y вАЦќЮ(z)вАЦ¬≤ = -2 ¬Ј вАЦќЮ(z)вАЦ¬≤ ¬Ј Im(ќЮ'(z)/ќЮ(z))`. The pole-witness engine
of ¬І¬І4вАУ6 handles the zero locus directly, so this is a viable
zero-removed reformulation. The calculus bridge to
`XiPullbackAntiHerglotzTarget` is a Mathlib `deriv`-on-`вАЦ¬ЈвАЦ¬≤` chase
deferred to a later phase. -/
def XiPullbackEnergyMonotoneAwayFromZeros : Prop :=
  вИА x y : вДЭ, 0 < y вЖТ
    XiPullback ((x : вДВ) + (y : вДВ) * Complex.I) вЙ† 0 вЖТ
      0 вЙ§ deriv
        (fun yy : вДЭ =>
          вАЦXiPullback ((x : вДВ) + (yy : вДВ) * Complex.I)вАЦ ^ 2) y

/-
**Kernel-energy inequality (NAMED OPEN TARGET / placeholder).**

The numerical double-kernel evidence rules out *pointwise* positivity of
the kernel `ќ¶(u)ќ¶(v)¬ЈK(u, v; x, y)` вАФ the integrand changes sign. The
actual analytic statement we need is the **integrated** inequality

  вИЂвИЂ ќ¶(u) ¬Ј ќ¶(v) ¬Ј K(u, v; x, y) du dv вЙ• 0    (for y > 0)

where `K` is the double-kernel arising from `вИВ_y вАЦќЮ(x + i¬Јy)вАЦ¬≤` when `ќЮ`
is written as the integral transform `ќЮ(z) = вИЂвВА^вИЮ ќ¶(u)¬Јcos(z¬Јu) du`.
That integrated form is the real analytic battlefield: a total-positivity
or de Branges-type theorem, not pointwise positivity.

The refactor below (CXXXV-E) defines `XiKernelEnergyInequality` as the
