-- ¬І17.B. Schwarz keystone вАФ Mellin transform of a real-valued function
-- ---------------------------------------------------------------------
-- Schwarz symmetry for `entireRiemannXi` reduces, via the Mathlib
-- `completedHurwitzZetaEvenвВА` chain, to a conjugation symmetry on the
-- Mellin transform of a real-valued function. The keystone is:
--
--   `mellin_star_ofReal : вИА (f : вДЭ вЖТ вДЭ) (s : вДВ),
--      mellin (fun t => (f t : вДВ)) (star s)
--        = star (mellin (fun t => (f t : вДВ)) s)`.
--
-- Once this lemma lands, it propagates up the FE-pair definition chain
-- (`completedHurwitzZetaEvenвВА 0 = (hurwitzEvenFEPair 0).ќЫвВА (s/2) / 2`,
--  whose underlying kernel `evenKernel` is `вДЭ вЖТ вДЭ`) to a Schwarz
-- symmetry on `completedRiemannZetaвВА`, then on `entireRiemannXi`.
--
-- This section proves the keystone. The FE-pair lift and final
-- discharge of `entireRiemannXi_schwarz_target` are deferred to ¬І17.C
-- (mechanical algebraic chain).

/-- в≠Р **PROVED вАФ Mellin transform of an `вДЭ вЖТ вДВ`-lifted real function
commutes with conjugation.** For any real-valued `f : вДЭ вЖТ вДЭ`,
`mellin (ofReal вИШ f) (star s) = star (mellin (ofReal вИШ f) s)`.

Proof: pull `star` (= complex conjugation) outside the integral via
`MeasureTheory.integral_conj`, then verify the per-point identity
`(t : вДВ) ^ (star s вИТ 1) вАҐ (f t : вДВ) = conj((t : вДВ) ^ (s вИТ 1) вАҐ (f t : вДВ))`
on `t вИИ Ioi 0` using:
* `Complex.cpow_conj` (with `(t : вДВ).arg = 0 вЙ† ѕА` for `t > 0`),
* `Complex.conj_ofReal` (for the real `f t`),
* `Complex.star_def` (`star = conj` on `вДВ`).

This is the *single* analytic content the ¬І17.C `entireRiemannXi`
Schwarz proof needs вАФ everything else is algebraic chain through the
`hurwitzEvenFEPair` definition. -/
theorem mellin_star_ofReal (f : вДЭ вЖТ вДЭ) (s : вДВ) :
    mellin (fun t : вДЭ => ((f t : вДЭ) : вДВ)) (star s)
      = star (mellin (fun t : вДЭ => ((f t : вДЭ) : вДВ)) s) := by
  unfold mellin
  -- Move star inside the RHS integral via integral_conj.
  rw [show star (вИЂ t in Set.Ioi (0 : вДЭ),
        ((t : вДВ) ^ (s - 1) вАҐ ((f t : вДЭ) : вДВ)))
      = вИЂ t in Set.Ioi (0 : вДЭ),
        star ((t : вДВ) ^ (s - 1) вАҐ ((f t : вДЭ) : вДВ))
      from (integral_conj
        (f := fun t : вДЭ => (t : вДВ) ^ (s - 1) вАҐ ((f t : вДЭ) : вДВ))
        (ќЉ := MeasureTheory.volume.restrict (Set.Ioi 0))).symm]
  -- Match integrands pointwise on Ioi 0.
  refine MeasureTheory.setIntegral_congr_fun measurableSet_Ioi ?_
  intro t ht
  -- Beta-reduce the lambda-wrapped goal.
  show (t : вДВ) ^ (star s - 1) вАҐ ((f t : вДЭ) : вДВ)
        = star ((t : вДВ) ^ (s - 1) вАҐ ((f t : вДЭ) : вДВ))
  have htpos : 0 < t := ht
  have h_arg : ((t : вДВ)).arg вЙ† Real.pi := by
    rw [Complex.arg_ofReal_of_nonneg htpos.le]
    exact (Real.pi_pos.ne').symm
  rw [Complex.star_def, smul_eq_mul, smul_eq_mul, map_mul, Complex.conj_ofReal]
  congr 1
  -- (t : вДВ) ^ (star s - 1) = conj((t : вДВ) ^ (s - 1))
  have h_cpow := Complex.cpow_conj (t : вДВ) (s - 1) h_arg
  rw [Complex.conj_ofReal] at h_cpow
  have h_sub : (starRingEnd вДВ) (s - 1) = (starRingEnd вДВ) s - 1 := by
    rw [map_sub, map_one]
  rw [вЖР h_sub]
  exact h_cpow

