-- =====================================================================
-- CLXXXVd-bis: Guarded (away-from-zeros) variants вАФ closes the `a/0=0`
-- gap in Route B's residual route.
-- =====================================================================
-- Background. `logDerivativeResponse f z := deriv f z / f z` totalizes
-- to `0` at zeros of `f` (Lean's `a / 0 = 0`). The ¬І6-bis engine guard
-- (`antiHerglotz_at_zero_is_vacuous`,
-- `antiHerglotz_iff_antiHerglotz_away_from_zeros`) shows the totalization
-- adds no proof obligation to the *sign law itself*. But Route B's
-- residual hypotheses `lowTErrorControlled` / `highTErrorControlled`
-- quantify over every band-`z` including hypothetical UHP zeros of ќЮ.
-- At a zero `ѕБ`, the algebra `error := ќЫ[ќЮ] вИТ M.model` forces
-- `|Im(error ѕБ)| = вИТIm(M.model ѕБ)` exactly, which the certificate's
-- strict slack `errorBound z < вИТIm(M.model z)` cannot accommodate.
-- Discharging the unguarded hypotheses therefore requires ruling out
-- UHP zeros вАФ i.e. RH вАФ making the conditional theorem effectively
-- RH-equivalent.
--
-- The fix is structural: keep `LocalXiCloudDensityErrorPackage` strong,
-- but weaken Route B's *input* predicates to demand the analytic bound
-- only where `XiPullback z вЙ† 0`. The zero case is handled internally
-- by a single algebra lemma.

/-- **Algebra at a zero of `XiPullback`.** If `ќЫ[ќЮ] z = M.model z + error z`
holds and `M.model` is anti-Herglotz on the UHP, then at any UHP zero of
`XiPullback` the totalization `ќЫ[ќЮ] ѕБ = 0` forces
`|Im(error ѕБ)| = вИТIm(M.model ѕБ)`, hence the margin inequality holds with
equality. This is the structural lemma that lets the analytic
hypotheses skip the zero case without going through the totalization. -/
theorem errorMargin_at_XiPullback_zero_of_decomp
    {M : CloudDensityTailModelDecomposition}
    {error : вДВ вЖТ вДВ}
    (hmodelAnti : AntiHerglotzUHP M.model)
    (hdecomp : вИА z : вДВ,
      logDerivativeResponse XiPullback z = M.model z + error z)
    {z : вДВ}
    (hz : 0 < z.im)
    (hzero : XiPullback z = 0) :
    |(error z).im| вЙ§ -(M.model z).im := by
  have hќЫ0 : logDerivativeResponse XiPullback z = 0 :=
    logDerivativeResponse_eq_zero_at_zero hzero
  have hsum : M.model z + error z = 0 := by
    calc
      M.model z + error z = logDerivativeResponse XiPullback z := by
        rw [hdecomp z]
      _ = 0 := hќЫ0
  have him : (error z).im = -(M.model z).im := by
    have h := congrArg Complex.im hsum
    simp [Complex.add_im] at h
    linarith
  have hnonneg : 0 вЙ§ -(M.model z).im := by
    have hm := hmodelAnti z hz
    linarith
  rw [him]
  exact le_of_eq (abs_of_nonneg hnonneg)

