-- =====================================================================
-- ¬ІCCLXXIX. Parameterized low residual explicit bound at `(T, ќ≥вВБ, D)`
-- =====================================================================
-- The ¬ІCCLXXVII pair hardcoded `(T, ќ≥вВБ, D) := (2ѕА, 14, 1/2)`, but the
-- numerical audit shows this is infeasible at the worst point
-- `(x, y) = (0, 4)`: residual bound вЙИ 0.77 vs model lower bound вЙИ 0.20.
-- This section parameterizes the low explicit bound and the
-- arithmetic obligation over `(T, ќ≥вВБ, D)` so a feasible combination
-- can be plugged in (current numerical candidate: `(10, 14, 2/5)`,
-- worst-point margin вЙИ 3.6√Ч10вБївБі; safer fallback: `(11, 14, 1/2)`,
-- worst-point margin вЙИ 9.7√Ч10вБї¬≥).
--
-- Adds:
--   lowResidualExplicitBoundAt                          вАФ parameterized closed form
--   lowResidualExplicitBound_eq_At                      вАФ specialization rfl
--   XiLowResidualExplicitDataAt                         вАФ residual вЙ§ explicit bound
--   LowMarginDominatesExplicitBoundAt                   вАФ explicit bound вЙ§ model margin
--   LowExplicitArithmeticBoundAt                        вАФ pure arithmetic obligation
--   XiLowResidualMargin_of_explicitAt_and_marginAt      вАФ bridge to XiLowResidualMargin
--   LowMarginDominatesExplicitBoundAt_twoPi_of_arithAt  вАФ _of_arith reduction
--   XiPullbackAntiHerglotzTarget_of_twoPiModel_lowExplicitAt
