-- then forces `xiResidualError M ѕБ = вИТM.model ѕБ` at any such zero, making
-- residual-equality / strict-bound hypotheses unprovable except by first
-- ruling out the zero (which is RH). The fix mirrors ¬І6-bis / ¬ІCCL-bis:
-- weaken the public analytic input by an explicit `XiPullback z вЙ† 0`
-- guard, and discharge the zero case internally with
-- `errorMargin_at_XiPullback_zero_of_decomp`.
