/-- рЯМЯ **PROVED вАФ regression: the zero-branch margin guard.** Names the
exact algebra step every guarded local-package constructor relies on in
its `XiPullback z = 0` branch. -/
theorem lowResidualMargin_zero_branch_guard_test
    {M : CloudDensityTailModelDecomposition}
    {z : вДВ}
    (hmodelAnti : AntiHerglotzUHP M.model)
    (hdecomp :
      вИА z : вДВ,
        logDerivativeResponse XiPullback z =
          M.model z + xiResidualError M z)
    (hz : 0 < z.im)
    (hzero : XiPullback z = 0) :
    |(xiResidualError M z).im| вЙ§ -(M.model z).im :=
  errorMargin_at_XiPullback_zero_of_decomp
    hmodelAnti hdecomp hz hzero

/-! ### Taint convention

`logDerivativeResponse XiPullback z` is the `a / 0 = 0` totalization of
`deriv (XiPullback) z / XiPullback z`. At any `z` with
`XiPullback z = 0`, the value collapses to `0` вАФ *not* the analytic
limit. `xiResidualError M z := logDerivativeResponse XiPullback z вИТ
M.model z` inherits this taint: at a zero, the residual is
*definitionally* `вИТM.model z`, regardless of any analytic interpretation.

Rule of thumb. Any public analytic input that mentions either
`logDerivativeResponse XiPullback z` or `xiResidualError M z` for `z`
ranging over a region of UHP must carry an explicit
`XiPullback z вЙ† 0 вЖТ` guard. The only places allowed to drop the guard
are trusted wrapper constructors that internally do
```
by_cases hzero : XiPullback z = 0
¬Ј exact errorMargin_at_XiPullback_zero_of_decomp ...
¬Ј exact analytic_input ... hzero
```
The ¬ІCCL-bis / ¬ІCCLXXXII / ¬ІCCLXXXVII chain implements this convention.
Discharge of an unguarded analytic input cannot proceed at a zero
without circularity. -/

-- =====================================================================
-- ¬ІCCLXXXVII. Discharge `Hgap` via structural `DzeroStartsAfter` + NвВА-root
-- =====================================================================
-- The ¬ІCCLXXXV `FirstZeroGapForDzero` Prop says
-- `finiteFluctuationPrimitive Dzero T0 u = -smoothZeroCountingN0 u`
-- on `[2ѕА, ќ≥]`. Under `DzeroStartsAfter ќ≥` (no fluctuation atoms in
-- `[T0, ќ≥]`) the discrete part vanishes and the structural identity
-- reduces to
--   `finiteFluctuationPrimitive Dzero T0 u
--      = smoothZeroCountingN0 T0 вИТ smoothZeroCountingN0 u`.
-- So the ¬ІCCLXXXV shape `= -NвВА(u)` holds **iff** `smoothZeroCountingN0 T0 = 0`,
-- i.e., iff `T0` is the unique root `uвВА вЙИ 9.74` of `NвВА` in `(2ѕА, вИЮ)`.
-- This section honestly carries that constraint as the `hN0_T0`
-- hypothesis. A future refactor could replace `FirstZeroGapForDzero`
-- with a basepoint-adjusted shape `S(T0, u) = NвВА(T0) вИТ NвВА(u)` that
-- accepts arbitrary `T0 вЙ§ 2ѕА`.
--
-- Adds:
--   DzeroStartsAfter                                      вАФ no atoms below ќ≥
--   discreteCountingPrimitive_eq_zero_of_startsAfter      вАФ discrete vanishes
--   smoothCountingPrimitive_eq_N0_diff                    вАФ FTC bridge
--   finiteFluctuationPrimitive_eq_N0_diff_of_startsAfter  вАФ structural identity
--   FirstZeroGapForDzero_of_startsAfter_at_root           вАФ inhabit Hgap
--   XiPullbackAntiHerglotzTarget_of_twoPiModel_lowFiniteIBP_11_14_half_startsAfter
--                                                          вАФ Hgap-free front door

/-- рЯУ¶ **`DzeroStartsAfter Dzero ќ≥`** вАФ strict structural condition:
every zero ordinate in `Dzero.Z` is strictly greater than `ќ≥`. For
`zeros100ceil` with first entry `15`, `DzeroStartsAfter Dzero 14`
holds (`14 < 15`). The strict inequality avoids edge cases at `u = ќ≥`. -/
structure DzeroStartsAfter
    (Dzero : Phase1IBP.OrderedFluctuationMeasureData) (ќ≥ : вДЭ) : Prop where
  z_gt_gamma : вИА i : вДХ, ќ≥ < Dzero.toFluctuationMeasureData.Z i

/-- в≠Р **PROVED вАФ discrete counting primitive vanishes on `[T0, u]`** when
all atoms lie strictly above `ќ≥ вЙ• u`. Each `if T0 вЙ§ Z_j вИІ Z_j вЙ§ u`
term is false because `u < Z_j`. -/
lemma discreteCountingPrimitive_eq_zero_of_startsAfter
    {Dzero : Phase1IBP.OrderedFluctuationMeasureData} {T0 ќ≥ u : вДЭ}
    (H : DzeroStartsAfter Dzero ќ≥) (hu : u вЙ§ ќ≥) :
    Phase1IBP.discreteCountingPrimitive
        Dzero.toFluctuationMeasureData T0 u = 0 := by
  classical
  unfold Phase1IBP.discreteCountingPrimitive
  apply Finset.sum_eq_zero
  intro j _
  have hZj : ќ≥ < Dzero.toFluctuationMeasureData.Z j := H.z_gt_gamma j
  have hu_Zj : u < Dzero.toFluctuationMeasureData.Z j :=
    lt_of_le_of_lt hu hZj
  have hnot :
      ¬ђ (T0 вЙ§ Dzero.toFluctuationMeasureData.Z j вИІ
         Dzero.toFluctuationMeasureData.Z j вЙ§ u) := by
    intro вЯ®_, hвЯ©
    exact (not_lt.mpr h) hu_Zj
  simp [hnot]

/-- в≠Р **PROVED вАФ `smoothCountingPrimitive T0 u = NвВА(u) вИТ NвВА(T0)`** for
positive `T0 вЙ§ u`, via FTC and `hasDerivAt_smoothZeroCountingN0`. -/
lemma smoothCountingPrimitive_eq_N0_diff
    {T0 u : вДЭ} (hT0 : 0 < T0) (hT0u : T0 вЙ§ u) :
    Phase1IBP.smoothCountingPrimitive T0 u
      = smoothZeroCountingN0 u - smoothZeroCountingN0 T0 := by
  unfold Phase1IBP.smoothCountingPrimitive
  have h_deriv : вИА v вИИ Set.uIcc T0 u,
      HasDerivAt smoothZeroCountingN0 (zeroDensityRho v) v := by
    intro v hv
    rw [Set.uIcc_of_le hT0u] at hv
    exact hasDerivAt_smoothZeroCountingN0
      (lt_of_lt_of_le hT0 hv.1)
  have h_int : IntervalIntegrable zeroDensityRho MeasureTheory.volume T0 u :=
    Phase1IBP.zeroDensityRho_intervalIntegrable hT0 hT0u
  exact intervalIntegral.integral_eq_sub_of_hasDerivAt h_deriv h_int

/-- в≠Р **PROVED вАФ structural identity for `finiteFluctuationPrimitive`**
on the first-zero gap under `DzeroStartsAfter`:
`S(T0, u) = NвВА(T0) вИТ NвВА(u)`. -/
theorem finiteFluctuationPrimitive_eq_N0_diff_of_startsAfter
    {Dzero : Phase1IBP.OrderedFluctuationMeasureData} {T0 ќ≥ u : вДЭ}
    (H : DzeroStartsAfter Dzero ќ≥)
    (hT0_pos : 0 < T0) (hT0u : T0 вЙ§ u) (hu : u вЙ§ ќ≥) :
    Phase1IBP.finiteFluctuationPrimitive Dzero T0 u
      = smoothZeroCountingN0 T0 - smoothZeroCountingN0 u := by
  unfold Phase1IBP.finiteFluctuationPrimitive
  rw [discreteCountingPrimitive_eq_zero_of_startsAfter H hu,
      smoothCountingPrimitive_eq_N0_diff hT0_pos hT0u]
  ring

/-- рЯМЯрЯМЯ **PROVED вАФ `FirstZeroGapForDzero Dzero T0 14` inhabitant** from
the structural pieces. Requires:
* `H : DzeroStartsAfter Dzero 14` вАФ no atoms below 14;
* `hT0_pos : 0 < T0`;
* `hT0_le_2pi : T0 вЙ§ 2ѕА` вАФ so the smooth-bridge integration on
  `[T0, u]` extends over the full gap `[2ѕА, 14]`;
* `hN0_T0 : smoothZeroCountingN0 T0 = 0` вАФ the basepoint-root condition
  needed to specialize the structural identity to the ¬ІCCLXXXV shape.

The `hN0_T0` hypothesis pins `T0` to the unique root `uвВА вЙИ 9.74` of
`NвВА` in `(2ѕА, вИЮ)`. A future refactor of ¬ІCCLXXXV's Hgap shape to
`S(T0, u) = NвВА(T0) вИТ NвВА(u)` would eliminate this constraint. -/
theorem FirstZeroGapForDzero_of_startsAfter_at_root
    {Dzero : Phase1IBP.OrderedFluctuationMeasureData} {T0 : вДЭ}
    (H : DzeroStartsAfter Dzero 14)
    (hT0_pos : 0 < T0)
    (hT0_le_2pi : T0 вЙ§ 2 * Real.pi)
    (hN0_T0 : smoothZeroCountingN0 T0 = 0) :
    FirstZeroGapForDzero Dzero T0 14 := by
  refine вЯ®?_вЯ©
  intro u hu_2pi hu14
  have hT0u : T0 вЙ§ u := le_trans hT0_le_2pi hu_2pi
  have h := finiteFluctuationPrimitive_eq_N0_diff_of_startsAfter
              H hT0_pos hT0u hu14
  rw [h, hN0_T0]
  ring

/-- рЯМЯрЯМЯрЯМЯрЯМЯрЯМЯрЯМЯрЯМЯрЯМЯрЯМЯрЯМЯрЯМЯрЯМЯрЯМЯрЯМЯрЯМЯрЯМЯрЯМЯрЯМЯрЯМЯрЯМЯрЯМЯрЯМЯрЯМЯрЯМЯрЯМЯрЯМЯрЯМЯрЯМЯрЯМЯрЯМЯ **PATH B
